+# PR 214 Review Reply Draft
+
+## T-214-01
+
+Fixed. The preview fallback payload now preserves both `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`, and `build_policy_preview(...)` normalizes `manual_review` before delegating to the preview builder. That keeps the fallback response aligned with the live preview shape after the reopen.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. This was the same reopened fallback regression, so the payload fix above resolves both threads.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Marked obsolete. The comment points at an outdated diff hunk, and I did not revive any legacy preview branch logic on the current branch. The remediation stays on the current path and does not add any legacy preview hint.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Fixed. Added a regression test in `tests/test_preview.py` covering `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state=\"manual_review\"`, and it now asserts the normalized `approval_state=\"human_review_required\"` together with `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Fixed. The approval policy doc now shows the corrected fallback payload, including `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
